    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 24 June 2004 vol 662 cc65-6WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_66ws' title='Col. 66WS &mdash; HL Deb 24 June 2004 vol 662 c66WS' name='column_66ws' href='#column_66ws' rel='bookmark'>66WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0662P0-07306'>
        <a name='S5LV0662P0_20040624_LWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-norman-warner' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0662P0_20040624_LWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr Norman Warner' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-norman-warner" title="Mr Norman Warner">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State, Department of Health (Lord Warner)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0662P0-07306">My honourable friend the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Community (Dr Stephen Ladyman) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement today.</p><p id="S5LV0662P0-07307">The Government's response to the Health Committee's Second Report of Session 2003&#x2013;04 on elder abuse, Cm 6270, has been published today. Copies have been placed in the Library.</p>
        </blockquote>
